Organisation of university-level studies, study forms and methods. Learning skills and self-reflection. Types of student papers, basics of their preparation and formal requirements. Practical lessons on preparing written papers. Basics of presentations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The learner acquires primary cognitive and metacognitive learning skills that form the basis for completing the curriculum, including preparing written papers and oral assignments.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the principles of university studies, forms of learning, how to plan their studies and are able to use e-learning environments;  2) knows different study methods and styles, are able to analyze their learning skills and further develop them; 3) knows the types of student papers and the general requirements for the preparation and formulation of the papers; 4) is able to find and present necessary information.
